[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1393},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":1368,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":1377},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20231013\u002F3280561145\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1352,"date":1353,"description":26,"extension":1354,"lang":1355,"meta":1356,"navigation":698,"path":1357,"readingMinutes":1358,"seo":1359,"standalone":1360,"stem":1361,"tags":1362,"tldr":1365,"updated":1353,"url":1366,"__hash__":1367},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication.md","Day 29 - About JWT Authentication","3479708607",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1341},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,37,40,50,54,65,68,96,113,116,125,128,150,154,157,173,178,181,189,192,200,204,207,276,279,287,290,301,304,315,318,341,344,394,401,405,408,454,457,493,496,528,531,565,568,575,578,586,595,601,604,607,610,984,987,993,996,999,1002,1006,1013,1031,1034,1129,1135,1146,1151,1154,1206,1213,1317,1320,1334,1337],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"About JWT authentication","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fisray_notarray_web_Certification_87b4aacf-552a-40c1-8cb8-9fa5dca7d52d.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"This post introduces JWT authentication. We haven't covered it before, but in real-world dev it's really important.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"authentication","Authentication",[12,32,33],{},"Why authenticate? In previous chapters, we didn't actually do any authentication mechanism — APIs, Discord, Chrome Extension, etc. — none of it. So why authenticate?",[12,35,36],{},"Some features in what we develop are restricted to specific people — admins, VIPs, etc. So we need a mechanism to authenticate identity. That's where JWT (JSON Web Token) comes in.",[12,38,39],{},"Modern mainstream development uses frontend-backend separation, not the traditional SSR (Server Side Rendering) architecture. The frontend mostly gets data via APIs the backend provides — and this data fetching needs to be authenticated.",[41,42,43],"blockquote",{},[12,44,45,49],{},[46,47,48],"strong",{},"Note","\nIn the early days, after a user logged in, the backend would store the user's UID in the server's memory (Session). But because modern mainstream development uses frontend-backend separation, this approach doesn't apply anymore — hence JWT.",[20,51,53],{"id":52},"what-is-json-web-token","What is JSON Web Token?",[12,55,56,57,64],{},"JWT stands for JSON Web Token — a widely used standard for authentication and authorization, especially in web development. It's also an open standard (",[58,59,63],"a",{"href":60,"rel":61},"https:\u002F\u002Fdatatracker.ietf.org\u002Fdoc\u002Fhtml\u002Frfc7519",[62],"nofollow","RFC 7519",").",[12,66,67],{},"JWT structure has three parts:",[69,70,71,80,88],"ul",{},[72,73,74,75],"li",{},"HEADER: ALGORITHM & TOKEN TYPE\n",[69,76,77],{},[72,78,79],{},"Indicates what algorithm encrypts this Token, and the Token type",[72,81,82,83],{},"PAYLOAD: DATA\n",[69,84,85],{},[72,86,87],{},"Mainly stores data — user ID, name, etc.",[72,89,90,91],{},"VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[69,92,93],{},[72,94,95],{},"Used to verify the Token is correct",[97,98,103],"pre",{"className":99,"code":100,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c\n","txt","",[104,105,106],"code",{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,108,111],"span",{"class":109,"line":110},"line",1,[107,112,100],{},[12,114,115],{},"Hard to see the difference right? Breaking it down by structure:",[97,117,119],{"className":99,"code":118,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},"HEADER.PAYLOAD.VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[104,120,121],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,122,123],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,124,118],{},[12,126,127],{},"With the JWT example above, it becomes:",[97,129,131],{"className":99,"code":130,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.  # HEADER\neyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ. # PAYLOAD\nSflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c # VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[104,132,133,138,144],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,134,135],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,136,137],{},"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.  # HEADER\n",[107,139,141],{"class":109,"line":140},2,[107,142,143],{},"eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ. # PAYLOAD\n",[107,145,147],{"class":109,"line":146},3,[107,148,149],{},"SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c # VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[20,151,153],{"id":152},"jwt-principles","JWT principles",[12,155,156],{},"How is JWT implemented? I mentioned the structure has three parts. The more core parts are PAYLOAD and VERIFY SIGNATURE. But let's go through all three. The example here uses the JWT Token from earlier:",[97,158,159],{"className":99,"code":130,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},[104,160,161,165,169],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,162,163],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,164,137],{},[107,166,167],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,168,143],{},[107,170,171],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,172,149],{},[174,175,177],"h3",{"id":176},"header","HEADER",[12,179,180],{},"HEADER mainly combines two parts:",[69,182,183,186],{},[72,184,185],{},"alg (Algorithm): encryption algorithm",[72,187,188],{},"typ (Type): Token type",[12,190,191],{},"These two parts get encoded into a Base64 string:",[97,193,194],{"className":99,"code":137,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},[104,195,196],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,197,198],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,199,137],{},[174,201,203],{"id":202},"payload","PAYLOAD",[12,205,206],{},"PAYLOAD is just a JSON object:",[97,208,212],{"className":209,"code":210,"language":211,"meta":102,"style":102},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"username\": \"Ray\", \u002F\u002F Username\n  \"email\": \"example.com\", \u002F\u002F Email\n  \"iat\": 1516239022 \u002F\u002F Issued At time\n}\n","json",[104,213,214,220,240,255,270],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,215,216],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,217,219],{"class":218},"sMAXC","{\n",[107,221,222,226,229,233,236],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,223,225],{"class":224},"sKpQp","  \"username\"",[107,227,228],{"class":218},": ",[107,230,232],{"class":231},"sTRMh","\"Ray\"",[107,234,235],{"class":218},", ",[107,237,239],{"class":238},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F Username\n",[107,241,242,245,247,250,252],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,243,244],{"class":224},"  \"email\"",[107,246,228],{"class":218},[107,248,249],{"class":231},"\"example.com\"",[107,251,235],{"class":218},[107,253,254],{"class":238},"\u002F\u002F Email\n",[107,256,258,261,263,267],{"class":109,"line":257},4,[107,259,260],{"class":224},"  \"iat\"",[107,262,228],{"class":218},[107,264,266],{"class":265},"sCcAr","1516239022",[107,268,269],{"class":238}," \u002F\u002F Issued At time\n",[107,271,273],{"class":109,"line":272},5,[107,274,275],{"class":218},"}\n",[12,277,278],{},"This JSON object gets encoded into Base64:",[97,280,281],{"className":99,"code":143,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},[104,282,283],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,284,285],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,286,143],{},[12,288,289],{},"PAYLOAD seems pretty simple right? But it's actually composed of three parts:",[69,291,292,295,298],{},[72,293,294],{},"Registered Claim",[72,296,297],{},"Public Claim",[72,299,300],{},"Private Claim",[12,302,303],{},"All three parts are optional, but in practice we usually use Public Claim to store data — user ID, name, etc.",[12,305,306,307,310,311,314],{},"Common settings include ",[104,308,309],{},"iat"," (Issued At) and ",[104,312,313],{},"exp"," (Expiration Time) in Registered Claim — these can be used to verify Token expiration.",[12,316,317],{},"Registered Claim has many properties:",[69,319,320,323,326,329,332,335,338],{},[72,321,322],{},"iss (Issuer)",[72,324,325],{},"sub (Subject)",[72,327,328],{},"aud (Audience)",[72,330,331],{},"exp (Expiration Time)",[72,333,334],{},"nbf (Not Before)",[72,336,337],{},"iat (Issued At)",[72,339,340],{},"jti (JWT ID)",[12,342,343],{},"So with the JSON object above:",[97,345,347],{"className":209,"code":346,"language":211,"meta":102,"style":102},"{\n  \"username\": \"Ray\", \u002F\u002F Username => Public Claim\n  \"email\": \"example.com\", \u002F\u002F Email => Public Claim\n  \"iat\": 1516239022 \u002F\u002F Issued At => Registered Claim\n}\n",[104,348,349,353,366,379,390],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,350,351],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,352,219],{"class":218},[107,354,355,357,359,361,363],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,356,225],{"class":224},[107,358,228],{"class":218},[107,360,232],{"class":231},[107,362,235],{"class":218},[107,364,365],{"class":238},"\u002F\u002F Username => Public Claim\n",[107,367,368,370,372,374,376],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,369,244],{"class":224},[107,371,228],{"class":218},[107,373,249],{"class":231},[107,375,235],{"class":218},[107,377,378],{"class":238},"\u002F\u002F Email => Public Claim\n",[107,380,381,383,385,387],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,382,260],{"class":224},[107,384,228],{"class":218},[107,386,266],{"class":265},[107,388,389],{"class":238}," \u002F\u002F Issued At => Registered Claim\n",[107,391,392],{"class":109,"line":272},[107,393,275],{"class":218},[41,395,396],{},[12,397,398,400],{},[46,399,48],{},"\nNote Claim is only three letters. Because JWT is designed to be concise and lightweight, Claim is only three letters.",[174,402,404],{"id":403},"verify-signature","VERIFY SIGNATURE",[12,406,407],{},"VERIFY SIGNATURE is encoding PAYLOAD and HEADER, then encrypting:",[97,409,413],{"className":410,"code":411,"language":412,"meta":102,"style":102},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","HMACSHA256(\n  base64UrlEncode(header) + \".\" +\n  base64UrlEncode(payload),\n  secret)\n","js",[104,414,415,424,442,449],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,416,417,421],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,418,420],{"class":419},"sj_SG","HMACSHA256",[107,422,423],{"class":218},"(\n",[107,425,426,429,432,436,439],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,427,428],{"class":419},"  base64UrlEncode",[107,430,431],{"class":218},"(header) ",[107,433,435],{"class":434},"sWyjQ","+",[107,437,438],{"class":231}," \".\"",[107,440,441],{"class":434}," +\n",[107,443,444,446],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,445,428],{"class":419},[107,447,448],{"class":218},"(payload),\n",[107,450,451],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,452,453],{"class":218},"  secret)\n",[12,455,456],{},"How does JWT know which algorithm to use for encryption? Through HEADER:",[97,458,460],{"className":209,"code":459,"language":211,"meta":102,"style":102},"{\n  \"alg\": \"HS256\",\n  \"typ\": \"JWT\"\n}\n",[104,461,462,466,479,489],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,463,464],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,465,219],{"class":218},[107,467,468,471,473,476],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,469,470],{"class":224},"  \"alg\"",[107,472,228],{"class":218},[107,474,475],{"class":231},"\"HS256\"",[107,477,478],{"class":218},",\n",[107,480,481,484,486],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,482,483],{"class":224},"  \"typ\"",[107,485,228],{"class":218},[107,487,488],{"class":231},"\"JWT\"\n",[107,490,491],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,492,275],{"class":218},[12,494,495],{},"If using PS256:",[97,497,499],{"className":209,"code":498,"language":211,"meta":102,"style":102},"{\n  \"alg\": \"PS256\",\n  \"typ\": \"JWT\"\n}\n",[104,500,501,505,516,524],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,502,503],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,504,219],{"class":218},[107,506,507,509,511,514],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,508,470],{"class":224},[107,510,228],{"class":218},[107,512,513],{"class":231},"\"PS256\"",[107,515,478],{"class":218},[107,517,518,520,522],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,519,483],{"class":224},[107,521,228],{"class":218},[107,523,488],{"class":231},[107,525,526],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,527,275],{"class":218},[12,529,530],{},"Then PAYLOAD and HEADER get encoded and encrypted:",[97,532,534],{"className":410,"code":533,"language":412,"meta":102,"style":102},"PS256(\n  base64UrlEncode(header) + \".\" +\n  base64UrlEncode(payload),\n  secret)\n",[104,535,536,543,555,561],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,537,538,541],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,539,540],{"class":419},"PS256",[107,542,423],{"class":218},[107,544,545,547,549,551,553],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,546,428],{"class":419},[107,548,431],{"class":218},[107,550,435],{"class":434},[107,552,438],{"class":231},[107,554,441],{"class":434},[107,556,557,559],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,558,428],{"class":419},[107,560,448],{"class":218},[107,562,563],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,564,453],{"class":218},[12,566,567],{},"This encrypted string also gets Base64-encoded.",[12,569,570,571,574],{},"What's ",[104,572,573],{},"secret","? A private key. When we generate a JWT Token, we need a private key to encrypt. When we verify a JWT Token, we need this private key to decrypt.",[12,576,577],{},"Another question — our generated JWT Token:",[97,579,580],{"className":99,"code":100,"language":101,"meta":102,"style":102},[104,581,582],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,583,584],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,585,100],{},[12,587,588,589,594],{},"You can throw this at ",[58,590,593],{"href":591,"rel":592},"https:\u002F\u002Fjwt.io\u002F",[62],"jwt.io"," and you'll find it auto-parses and tells you what algorithm encrypted this Token and the Token type:",[12,596,597],{},[15,598],{"alt":599,"src":600},"JWT Token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fjwt_token.png",[12,602,603],{},"OK problem:",[12,605,606],{},"\"Why can it parse without us providing the private key (secret)?\"",[12,608,609],{},"Because JWT Token is just Base64-encoded — not encrypted. So you can write your own JWT Token parser. Here's a simple example:",[97,611,613],{"className":410,"code":612,"language":412,"meta":102,"style":102},"\u002F\u002F Base64 decode\nconst Base64decoded = (str) => {\n  str = str.replace(\u002F-\u002Fg, '+').replace(\u002F_\u002Fg, '\u002F');\n\n  \u002F\u002F Pad with \"=\" if length isn't a multiple of 4\n  while (str.length % 4 !== 0) {\n    str += '=';\n  }\n\n  return window.atob(str);\n}\n\n\u002F\u002F Parse JWT Token\nconst jwtTokenEncoded = (str) => {\n  if(!str) return console.log('Please input JWT Token');\n  const [header, payload, signature] = str.split('.');\n\n  const headerDecoded = JSON.parse(Base64decoded(header));\n  const payloadDecoded = JSON.parse(Base64decoded(payload));\n\n  return {\n    header: headerDecoded,\n    payload: payloadDecoded,\n  }\n}\n\njwtTokenEncoded('eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c')\n",[104,614,615,620,647,694,700,705,732,747,753,758,773,778,783,789,809,839,876,881,908,931,936,943,949,955,960,965,970],{"__ignoreMap":102},[107,616,617],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,618,619],{"class":238},"\u002F\u002F Base64 decode\n",[107,621,622,625,628,631,634,638,641,644],{"class":109,"line":140},[107,623,624],{"class":434},"const",[107,626,627],{"class":419}," Base64decoded",[107,629,630],{"class":434}," =",[107,632,633],{"class":218}," (",[107,635,637],{"class":636},"s_sBn","str",[107,639,640],{"class":218},") ",[107,642,643],{"class":434},"=>",[107,645,646],{"class":218}," {\n",[107,648,649,652,655,658,661,664,667,670,672,675,677,679,681,684,686,688,691],{"class":109,"line":146},[107,650,651],{"class":218},"  str ",[107,653,654],{"class":434},"=",[107,656,657],{"class":218}," str.",[107,659,660],{"class":419},"replace",[107,662,663],{"class":218},"(",[107,665,666],{"class":231},"\u002F-\u002F",[107,668,669],{"class":434},"g",[107,671,235],{"class":218},[107,673,674],{"class":231},"'+'",[107,676,64],{"class":218},[107,678,660],{"class":419},[107,680,663],{"class":218},[107,682,683],{"class":231},"\u002F_\u002F",[107,685,669],{"class":434},[107,687,235],{"class":218},[107,689,690],{"class":231},"'\u002F'",[107,692,693],{"class":218},");\n",[107,695,696],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,697,699],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":698},true,"\n",[107,701,702],{"class":109,"line":272},[107,703,704],{"class":238},"  \u002F\u002F Pad with \"=\" if length isn't a multiple of 4\n",[107,706,708,711,714,717,720,723,726,729],{"class":109,"line":707},6,[107,709,710],{"class":434},"  while",[107,712,713],{"class":218}," (str.",[107,715,716],{"class":265},"length",[107,718,719],{"class":434}," %",[107,721,722],{"class":265}," 4",[107,724,725],{"class":434}," !==",[107,727,728],{"class":265}," 0",[107,730,731],{"class":218},") {\n",[107,733,735,738,741,744],{"class":109,"line":734},7,[107,736,737],{"class":218},"    str ",[107,739,740],{"class":434},"+=",[107,742,743],{"class":231}," '='",[107,745,746],{"class":218},";\n",[107,748,750],{"class":109,"line":749},8,[107,751,752],{"class":218},"  }\n",[107,754,756],{"class":109,"line":755},9,[107,757,699],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":698},[107,759,761,764,767,770],{"class":109,"line":760},10,[107,762,763],{"class":434},"  return",[107,765,766],{"class":218}," window.",[107,768,769],{"class":419},"atob",[107,771,772],{"class":218},"(str);\n",[107,774,776],{"class":109,"line":775},11,[107,777,275],{"class":218},[107,779,781],{"class":109,"line":780},12,[107,782,699],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":698},[107,784,786],{"class":109,"line":785},13,[107,787,788],{"class":238},"\u002F\u002F Parse JWT Token\n",[107,790,792,794,797,799,801,803,805,807],{"clas